<h1>Help</h1>

<h2>What is ScholarSphere?</h2>
<p>
Penn State's ScholarSphere is a research repository service beginning to collect scholarly work from faculty, staff and students in September 2012.  It is being developed and supported in a partnership of the University Libraries and Digital Library Technologies, a division of Information Technology Services.  It enables members of the Penn State community including faculty, staff, and students to increase the visibility of their research and to share their scholarly work more widely.
</p>

<p>
Researchers can actively manage stored versions of their research and preserve it, ensuring its longevity over time for future generations of scholars to find, use, and build on. A trusted institutional service, ScholarSphere has safeguards in place for keeping private research secure and unchanged over time . The service allows the depositor to set the level of access possible by others. 
</p>

