Questions about ScholarSphere? Contact the project team: DLT-GAMMA-PROJECT@lists.psu.edu ﻿ [this will change as we get helps in place]
</p>

<h2>How would I use it?</h2>
<p>
As a contributor, since anyone in the Penn State community involved in the research process will be able to deposit scholarly materials there. These might include project results, numeric data, videos, student theses and capstone projects, and other types of digital formats.
</p>

<p>
As a source of scholarly information, since it will have access to the work (text data, media, etc.) that other Penn State researchers contribute.
</p>

<h2>Why should I deposit my work in ScholarSphere?</h2>
<p>
 Visibility for your research contributions.  Researchers can make digitized materials available easily for others to locate, setting a range of retrieval options from full access to just an indication that particular data exists.
 </p>

 <p>
 Authoritative way to manage materials you submit.  Each item will be assigned an individual persistent identifier (“address”) so that it can be cited and retrieved, prior versions are accessible for editing, many formats are accepted, access level is set by the contributor.
 Long term storage and preservation.   You will participate in a program that supports preservation and access over time. Meet the data management plan requirements mandated by grant funding agencies. 
 </p>

